I am using [Windows Management Infrastructure (MI)][1] to perform a number of tasks by making API calls directly from C#.  Many of the CIM operations and ctors take an instance of `CimOperationOptions`.  I have found very few examples of code which provides these options (and no documentation) and don&#39;t know when they are to be used, and what is valid to provide.

I had to provide `CimOperationOptions` when creating an IPSec tunnel rule, but I only knew that because I pulled apart the `New-NetIPsecRule` cmdlet.  That example was not enough to generally understand what the options are used for, nor what are valid values to provide.   `CimOperationOptions.SetCustomOption()` &quot;sets a custom server or CIM provider option&quot;.  But I can&#39;t find any reference for what those options are, or how to determine them.  So I don&#39;t know of a way to determine if I need to pass values via `CimOperationOptions` again (if I can&#39;t find a cmdlet to unwind).

Can someone explain what the options control, and how to know what values can be safely provided?

